      "title": "Foundations of Object-Oriented Programming in Java",
      "content": "Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) is a programming paradigm based on the concept of objects.",
      "layout": {
        "bullets": [
          "Encapsulation: Bundles data and methods that operate on the data within a single unit (class).",
          "Abstraction: Hides complex implementation details and shows only essential features.",
          "Inheritance: Allows a new class to inherit properties and behavior from an existing class.",
          "Polymorphism: Enables a single interface to represent different underlying forms (data types)."
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
}
